commit.title: Fix printing of raw terms for lambda's without parameters
commit.message:
Fix printing of raw terms for lambda's without parameters

When parsing terms, sometimes lambda's without any variables are
inserted. These lambdas are detected and removed when globalizing
the AST in the function Constrintern.internalize. However, when
printing raw AST's the empty lambda's are still there and cause
the code to crash. Example term: let x := 1 in True.
